Today, the Government responded to the latest escape by ruling that prisoners with a history of escaping will
 no longer be placed in open prisons.

It is the latest in a series of 
escapes that has heaped embarrassment on ministers and prompted critics 
to brand the prison service ‘beyond a joke’.

